node.text:
How was your Summit experience? I loved every moment and can’t wait till next year Summit in St. Louis 🔥
That will be our first live Summit in two years and i can speak for the rest of the trainers we miss you guys! There’s nothing better than doing a 90 minute leg workout with you guys 😩 If you worked out with us virtually show love and drop a 🙌🏿 and tell me what you loved about it! @beachbody

node.text:
These are the moments i live for and i am so proud of you! You showed up for yourself every day. You grew physically and most importantly, mentally. The mindset shift looks at everything as an opportunity — every “failure” is just feedback; every challenge is an occasion to learn; every problem is an invitation to invent a new solution. @645 challenged you and came out stronger with a whole new mindset! 

Congrats @tinamarieflores 🔥 

Drop a 🙌🏿

node.title: Let’s take a moment to praise @tinamarieflores 👸

node.text:
I love you papa! You’re the strongest man i know. My father took a boat from Haiti to America to earn money so he could send back to his family. Everything he’s done has been for us. He consistently encouraged me to study hard so I could someday go to college. When I graduated UCF he had the biggest smile on his face and i was just happy to make him proud! If anyone knows him he’s always talking to his Co-workers about his kids they know so much about us it’s not even funny lol. He sacrificed a lot.  People like my father make you come alive. They make you dream. 

Happy Father’s Day 💙

Also we know dad loves you more @nicci_cesar 😂😂

📽 @ajlising @octoman 
“DEAR LENORA” coming soon 🎬

node.text:
645 we grind 😤 6 days a week 45 minutes a day let’s go get it! I can’t wait to get back to work with you guys! 
645 is my new @beachbody program name. This program combines strength training, cardio, and mobility work using functional, powerful moves that will target your entire body. This program has a Personal training aspect to make you feel like i’m right next you. With more focus on strength and balanced movement. I love the way we are shooting it feels more personal and interactive with the viewer and cast! 

If you’re ready to get back to it drop a 😤

Directed 📽 by @ajlising da 🐐 thank you brother! 🙏🏿

DP 📽 @octoman 

#beachbody #645

Also somebody come get @shytime 😭😭

node.text:
Does your movement competency allow you to be adaptable? I read a lot to Gray Cook and we share alot of similarities in thoughts. One passage that stuck with me was how our  relationship to our environment is unique. 

“Historically, the environment forced us to adapt since our ability to modify our surroundings was limited. Today we seem to resist natural and practical adaptation  we modify every part of the environment that touches us. We modify our most common activities to make every aspect of being active totally comfortable and convenient with a minimal learning curve. Unfortunately, comfort does not seem to foster or stimulate adaptation. Stress is a teacher, but we seem to want our stress meal to be served in bite-sized, sugarcoated portions. We want tension on our leg muscles, but we hate all the technical precision required to squat so we invented the leg press. We seemed to forget that the ability to produce tension without the ability to control our posture and balance has no practical advantage in nature.”

So learn how to truly control your body and adapt 💙 i talk a lot about this in @645program 

📽 @ajlising
